    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Oil Pump Spline Drive</title>
        <figure id="f3350016508" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5224.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil pump spline drive removal</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, during oil pump spline drive removal, strike chisel carefully to prevent
                    damage to the crankshaft.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para id="s1606" count="1">Place a chisel between the oil pump spline drive teeth and carefully strike
                chisel with a hammer to split the spline drive.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the oil pump spline drive from the crankshaft.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
